Kaizer Chiefs' 2-1 defeat to Mariztburg United at FNB Stadium on Saturday has left Amakhosi coach Ernst Middendorp lost for words. JOHANNESBURG - Kaizer Chiefs dropped valuable points in their 2-1 defeat to Mariztburg United at FNB Stadium on Saturday. The result left Amakhosi coach Ernst Middendorp lost for words. READ: Kaizer Chiefs celebrate 50 years Chiefs' lead at the top of the table is down to seven points ahead of Mamelodi Sundowns, who have a game in hand. Kaizer Chiefs will hope to redeem themselves when they play their arch rivals Orlando Pirates on 29 February. 